## Calculating Module Seat Time

| Screen types | Average number of words | Approximate duration (minutes) |
|-------------|------------------------|-------------------------------|
| Text and image | 150 | 1 |
| Text and image (module/topic title screens) | 1 - 5 | 3 seconds |
| Click and reveal (with on screen popups) | 270 | 1.5 |
| Click and reveal (with FULL screen popups) | 400 | 2.5 |
| Multi choice question (including feedback popups) | 220 | 1.5 |
| Time based media (video, audio, animation) | — | Total media length |

> **Estimates are based on the following logic:**
> - **Self-paced reading**: The average speed it takes an adult to read from a screen is **220 words per minute (wpm)**. This gives you the minimum amount of time to complete a module. However, learners may require more time to consider and review answers, review previous screens etc, therefore an extra **25% of time** is added to get a more accurate estimation of total completion time.
> - **Pre-recorded voiceover**: The average speed it takes an adult to speak text is **120 wpm**. Allow an extra **10% of time** for natural pauses and breaks.
